args: Jeez Slick, you're really swingin' for\nthe fences!
How'd ya get that strong, anyway?\nGood ol' fashioned willpower, is it?
Heh. That's not far off, actually.
I've always had people I wanted to protect,\nand that's what made me want to get\nstronger.
In the end, that desire to protect others\nactually BECAME my strength.
Hm, maybe I wasn't clear enough.
Basically, I've come to realize that the\nsecret to strength is to fight FOR someone.
You have people in your life that you\nwant to protect, right?
Mm, not too sure about that.
What about your parents? Don't you want\nto protect them?
Ah, well... I haven't seen 'em in a while.\nI left home after we got into this big scrap.
They tried to stop me from doin' my hair\nlike this. Can you believe that?!
Still, I'm sure you'll understand eventually\nif you keep fighting.
You sayin' I gotta get in more scraps?\nShoulda led with that, Slick!
Can't get better at fightin' unless you\nfight MORE, right? Makes perfect sense!
I better get movin' so.\nCOME AT ME, TURKEYS!
I wonder... Does he try to act tough to hide\nthe fear he holds deep down?
What's the haps, Red Champ?\n...Wait, what's that?!
Yowch, that's one big turkey.\nYou got this, Red Champ!
There's that glare! You don't know what's\ncomin', fiend—
Damn, he didn't even flinch...\nThat's hardcore, man!
Hah! That all you got, wimp?\nRed Champ didn't even FEEL that!
Damn... He's takin' every blow,\njust to protect his chicks!
In the end, that desire to protect others\nactually BECAME my strength.
I think I finally get it.
I feel the answer burnin' in my heart!
I've got your back, Red Champ.\nWhatever's important to you is\nimportant to me too!
So I'm gonna fight with you.\nTake THIS!
But I won't let myself be scared!
Let's wrap this up.\nEAT METAL, SCUMBAG! HIYA!
DAMN I'm strong! Ha ha ha!
You and the kids see that, Red Champ?!
With my chariot, and my will to protect\npeople, nothin' can...
(As long as I was riding my chariot,\nI felt invincible.)
(No fiend could take me on, no matter\nhow strong!)
(We were together on the coldest\nof nights...)
(And man, when we got goin', we were\nlike the damn wind.)
(There was that time we rode to the next\ntown over to try their famous bread... Still\nthe best I've ever had!)
(Hell, we even FLEW together! I really\nshoulda seen that cliff...)
Can I even fight without you, partner?!
I can't go back to my lame old\nself again... I can't!
